Super John:<br><br>
SW hit the nail on the head..Good post, Ozone Breath!<br><br>
The down side is what the war did to Daddies!  Daddies with serious interpersonal relationship skills could and can not get along with Mommies and Kiddies.  It shows up in our growing divorce rate... behavior disorders and attention deficiet disorders in our teeny boppers (there goes a big dent in our future!)<br>
Lots of unresolved anger = lots of depression = lots of immobilization = poor work ethic = piss poor performance = bad impact on the GNP!<br>
It does branch out to populate the prisons and fill the underpasses with the homeless.. and generate suicides and a lot of other bad stuff.  Dads who are suffering from their private maladies attributable to PTSD, but often unspecific, do not provide the necessary leadership to assure strong homes.. raise healthy kids and stand guard over morals and values.  Some of the three million did okay when they came home.. some not so good and some piss poor.  There are those who have woke up... those who are waking up (late in life) and those who are lost.<br>
The war made a few indestructable and a bunch self-destructing... with a wide swath of confused in between.<br>
Personally, I think you are one of the good ones, John.<br><br>
MTF
